context_history.content: I want to learn about: css. DO NOT greet me. Immediately start lesson Step 1 by explaining the core concept on the whiteboard.

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is the language used to style the visual presentation of a web page. It acts as the 'skin' or 'clothing' that wraps around the HTML 'skeleton' to define colors, layouts, and fonts.

visual_content.detail: HTML (Structure), CSS (Style), Final Website, CSS applies visual rules to structural elements.
